0million%2C%20down%20from%20its%201979%20peak%20of%2019.5%20million.%20To%20get%20back%20to%20that%20mark%2C%20the%20US%20would%20need%20to%20add%20roughly%206.7%20million%20jobs.%20Wells%20Fargo%20added%20that%20the%20figure%20is%20nearly%20the%20same%20as%20the%20entire%20pool%20of%20unemployed%20Americans%2C%20which%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fempsit.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApril%20was%207.2%20million%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPopulation%20aging%2C%20negative%20perceptions%2C%20and%20skill%20mismatches%20also%20underpin%20workforce%20concerns%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20Fargo%20analysts%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BNew%20jobs%20will%20require%20different%20skills%20than%20those%20previously%20lost.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20Taiwanese%20chipmaker%20TSMC%20said%20it%20delayed%20the%20opening%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsmc-arizona-semiconductor-chip-fab-taiwan-china-president-joe-biden-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EArizona%20chip%20factory%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20a%20shortage%20of%20skilled%20workers.%20A%20report%20released%20in%20April%202024%20by%20Deloitte%20and%20the%20Manufacturing%20Institute%20also%20found%20that%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%203.8%20million%20new%20manufacturing%20jobs%20anticipated%20by%202033%20could%20remain%20unfilled%20due%20to%20skill%20gaps%20and%20other%20population%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTariffs%20must%20be%20high%20enough%20to%20make%20the%20cost%20of%20domestic%20production%20competitive%20in%20the%20US%20market%2C%20and%20they%20also%20must%20be%20kept%20in%20place%20long%20enough%20for%20producers%20to%20bring%20on%20additional%20workers%20and%20expand%20capacity%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20concluded.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20economic%20or%20political%20costs%20are%20deemed%20too%20high%2C%20the%20current%20administration%